sentences: In 1935, Almeida and Martinez recorded a single for Bluebird Records, "La Chicharronera" b/w "El Troconal" (the former a polka and the latter a schottische).
The duo would record extensively for Bluebird, releasing some 60 additional singles for the label between 1935 and 1938.
In the 1940s, the pair continued to record for Ideal Records and Disco de Oro.
He moved to Sunnyside, Washington in 1950, working as an apple picker and music teacher.
Almeida died July 8, 1999 in Sunnyside, Washington.
In 1987, his contributions to music were recognized when he was inducted into the Conjunto Hall of Fame in San Antonio.
In 1993 he was awarded the Governor's Heritage Award in Washington.
In 2005, he was inducted posthumously into the Texas Conjunto Music Hall of Fame and Museum in San Benito.
By the late 1940s, Almeida had amassed a large family and found his musical success more difficult to sustain.

sentences: Santiago Almeida (July 25, 1911 – July 8, 1999) was a Texas musician influential in the development of the musical genres of tejano and conjunto.
He continued to perform locally at gatherings and in churches for the next several decades.
He was also a 1993 recipient of a National Heritage Fellowship from the National Endowment for the Arts, which is the highest honor in the folk and traditional arts in the United States.
